pageContext.claim: “Energy exports are at a record high, and foreign imports are at their lowest level in much more than a decade.”
pageContext.analysis: Energy exports are in fact at a record high. But import levels are not as low as Trump claims. The United States imported 25.34 quadrillion BTUs of energy in 2017, according to the Energy Information Administration. Imports were lower in 2015, 2014 and 2013.
